Russia Rugby Coach Resigns Before Australia Defeat, RIA Reports

-- B y   A l e n a   C h e c h e l
-- 
2011-10-01T14:58:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/russia-rugby-coach-resigns-before-australia-defeat-ria-reports.html
Russia ’s rugby team coach Nikolay
Nerush resigned as Russia finished at the bottom of its group in
the  World Cup , RIA Novosti said, citing the Russian coach.  Nerush announced his decided to step down before today’s
68-22 loss to Australia in the last Pool C match, the news
service said. Russia, which was playing in its first World Cup,
lost its other three games to Italy, Ireland and the U.S.  Nerush, who has headed the Russian rugby team for three
years, declined to give details, RIA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alena Chechel in Moscow at 
 achechel@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net . 